Match State: Lunch - Day 1

Welcome back to our coverage of the first day's play of the fourth Ashes Test at Trent Bridge

The news isn't great at the moment. As we had suggested before the start of play, there is a bit of rain aroun.

A heavy shower during the lunch break has meant that the covers are on

Fortunately the groundstaff were alert to the possibility and had the covers on before the raingot heavy

They are now working hard to get the field of play ready

We're unable to tell you exactly when that will be, but can assure you that you won't miss a ball of the action if you stay with Cricinfo.

We'll be right here, monitoring the situation closely and updating you with the news as and when there is some

Hello and welcome to the start of the fourth Ashes Test

I'm Anand Vasu, and will be your commentator for this game. It has been tremendously enjoyable calling the action for the first three Tests and one can only hope this turns out to be a cracker as well

Let's cut to the chase and give you all the news as it has come in

England have won the toss and chosen to bat

But the news for Austgralia is not so good. Glenn McGrath has been ruled out and Michael Kasprowicz takes his place

Jason Gillespie, who has struggled for form all summer has been left out, and Shaun Tait, the young tearaway from South Australia gets his Test debut

The weather forecasts have been a bit iffy for the next few days

There's rain in the area and we expect interruptions in the form of showers

With the series standing at 1-1 there's everything to play for here. The Ashes could well be decided on how the day's play goes

There's been plenty of excitement surrounding Shaun Tait, who is reputed to regularly clock in excess of 90 mph

The players are all on the field now and onm place

The umpire calls "Play!"
